WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.880
Title: (Re)Figuring Citation:
Metaphors, Performance, and

00:00:02.880 --> 00:00:05.729
Transformative Use / Daniel Anderson
iamdan@unc.edu @iamdan.

00:00:05.959 --> 00:00:10.689
A web page with a video appears.

00:00:10.881 --> 00:00:13.386
The cursor hovers the play button.

00:00:13.564 --> 00:00:16.634
Title on screen: First Metaphor:
Private Property.

00:00:16.705 --> 00:00:19.555
The cursor clicks play.
The video shows a message:

00:00:19.764 --> 00:00:22.754
This video contains content from
Warner Bros. Entertainment,

00:00:22.754 --> 00:00:26.244
who has blocked it on copyright grounds.

00:00:26.553 --> 00:00:30.293
A web page shows a forum posting
on YouTube's copyright algorithm.

00:00:30.587 --> 00:00:34.317 line:1
A passage is highlighted: I'm wondering
how the algorithm correctly identifies

00:00:34.317 --> 00:00:37.894 line:1
the song as infringing copyright.

00:00:37.965 --> 00:00:41.265 line:1
A student video fills the screen
with a fish surfacing on a lake.

00:00:41.346 --> 00:00:45.506
The video shows text on screen
and fishing imagery.

00:00:46.134 --> 00:00:49.714 line:1
Fishing boots in the video shift to a
male figure walking away in a meadow.

00:00:49.955 --> 00:00:53.615 line:1
The video shows text: Two songs.

00:00:53.932 --> 00:00:57.902 line:1
A cursor types in a note: Writers commonly
focused on . . . between 3 and 13

00:00:57.902 --> 00:01:02.765 line:1
[criteria] when accounting for their
citing decisions. . . . Different authors

00:01:02.765 --> 00:01:08.265 line:1
had different priorities, and one of the 
distinctions . . . was the authors'

00:01:08.265 --> 00:01:16.215 line:1
identification with the "researcher"
or "teacher" role.

00:01:16.455 --> 00:01:20.995 line:1
The video shows text: A shape
already inside a shape.

00:01:21.581 --> 00:01:25.215 line:1
A scan from the MLA style guide appears
showing questions to ask when citing:

00:01:25.215 --> 00:01:27.705 line:1
Who, What, How, When, Where, Why.

00:01:27.940 --> 00:01:33.185
The scan is overlaid with imagery of a
fisherman walking through a meadow.

00:01:36.658 --> 00:01:40.273 line:1
A translucent rectangle appears; beneath
it appear a lake surface and text:

00:01:40.273 --> 00:01:42.128 line:1
a rise on a small lake.

00:01:42.468 --> 00:01:45.228 line:1
Fishing imagery appears in the background.

00:01:46.008 --> 00:01:49.488 line:1
a cursor types in the rectangle:
Citation is a private and subjective

00:01:49.488 --> 00:01:53.248 line:1
process, and motivations/functions cannot
straightforwardly be read off by the

00:01:53.248 --> 00:02:00.156 line:1
textual analyst, however specialized
his/her knowledge.

00:02:01.777 --> 00:02:05.217 line:1
A title appears:
Second Metaphor: Favorites.

00:02:06.047 --> 00:02:10.047
A web browser appears showing videos
from a YouTube search.

00:02:13.714 --> 00:02:17.374
The curosor clicks a video thumbnail
and images fill the screen: a waterfall,

00:02:17.487 --> 00:02:23.804 line:1
trees, grasses, ruins, moose.

00:02:24.005 --> 00:02:28.005 line:1
The screen fills with a video editor
showing a student project.

00:02:28.273 --> 00:02:32.883 line:1
The video shows typing: I had A LOT of fun
editing my clips!

00:02:33.929 --> 00:02:37.519 line:1
A rectangle appears with typing: I gave
nods to some of my favorite movies

00:02:37.519 --> 00:02:41.319 line:1
through some of the more subtle clips. The
"Sufi poet" is actually Tom Hanks

00:02:41.319 --> 00:02:46.640 line:1
in the film "Cloud Atlas," which is my
favorite book!

00:02:46.885 --> 00:02:49.155 line:1
The video editor shows
the student project.

00:02:49.659 --> 00:02:53.179 line:1
A rectangle appears with typing: The
"garden of dust" is actually a shot

00:02:53.179 --> 00:02:55.899 line:1
of Jakku from "Star Wars:
The Force Awakens!"

00:02:56.197 --> 00:02:58.827 line:1
The video editor shows
the student project.

00:02:59.436 --> 00:03:03.096 line:1
A rectangle appears with typing: But one
of the most fun clips to select was

00:03:03.096 --> 00:03:09.436 line:1
this one. I felt as though the
"everything" needed to be EPIC

00:03:09.755 --> 00:03:15.105 line:1
So I searched YouTube for
"COOL SPACE EXPLOSIONS"

00:03:15.286 --> 00:03:19.496
In the YouTube search field, the cursor
types: COOL SPACE EXPLOSIONS.

00:03:19.936 --> 00:03:22.996
Search results fill the screen
showing space explosions.

00:03:23.237 --> 00:03:27.237
The screen fades to white.

00:03:28.242 --> 00:03:31.422
A web browser fills the screen.

00:03:31.622 --> 00:03:39.562
The browser shows imagery of a basketball
and net and text: March Madness.

00:03:40.150 --> 00:03:42.540
The cursor loads a new tab in the browser.

00:03:43.034 --> 00:03:48.395
An image of young woman appears.

00:03:51.408 --> 00:03:55.168
The screen fades to white.

00:03:55.694 --> 00:03:59.694
A video editor fills the screen showing
a student project.

00:04:02.140 --> 00:04:09.538
The editor shows aerial views
of grasses, trees, and rolling hills.

00:04:11.452 --> 00:04:15.632
In the student project, text appears:
Look down upon Captivity --

00:04:16.115 --> 00:04:23.905 line:1
The playhead in the editor moves along the
timeline as the footage plays.

00:04:26.755 --> 00:04:32.295
In the student project, text appears:
And laugh -- No more have I --

00:04:37.246 --> 00:04:41.246
In the aerial footage, the camera rotates
and sunlight flares across the landscape.

00:04:44.853 --> 00:04:48.853
In the student project, text appears:
A Poem by Emily Dickinson.

00:04:51.367 --> 00:04:55.187
In the student project, text appears:
Edited by Emily Dickinson Shepherd.

00:04:55.547 --> 00:04:58.947
The screen fades to white, then
a cursor types: Digital craft criticism

00:04:58.947 --> 00:05:05.457
imagines what choices made at the
material level contribute not only to the

00:05:05.457 --> 00:05:12.219
interpretation of the text that requires
reading, watching and listening, but,

00:05:12.219 --> 00:05:17.409 line:1
more important, the limits and horizons
that particular material conditions

00:05:17.409 --> 00:05:27.329 line:1
in digital environments
make possible for imaginative texts.

00:05:34.477 --> 00:05:36.627 line:1
The screen fades to white.

00:05:36.747 --> 00:05:40.747 line:1
A scan from a book appears.

00:05:42.828 --> 00:05:47.418
The screen slowly zooms in on text
from the scan: The source being documented

00:05:47.418 --> 00:05:50.348
forms a part of. . . .

00:05:50.700 --> 00:05:54.270
The larger whole can be thought of
as a container. . . .

00:05:55.939 --> 00:05:59.939 line:1
The screen continues to zoom in on text:
The container is crucial.

00:06:03.588 --> 00:06:08.898 line:1
The screen continues
to zoom in on text.

00:06:11.328 --> 00:06:15.328 line:1
Title appears on screen:
Third Metaphor: Listening.

00:06:16.944 --> 00:06:19.639 line:1
A web browser appear showing video
thumbnails.

00:06:20.258 --> 00:06:23.198 line:1
The cursor loads a video titled
Make Your Own Lanyard.

00:06:23.482 --> 00:06:27.362 line:1
A rectangle appears with typing:
Advocating a context-is-the-new-content

00:06:27.362 --> 00:06:31.532 line:1
approach to the understanding of creative
writing, Goldsmith proposes what he calls

00:06:31.532 --> 00:06:37.532 line:1
uncreative writing: "focused on . . . 
'manipulation' and 'management'

00:06:37.532 --> 00:06:44.478 line:1
of the heaps of already existent
and ever-increasing language."

00:06:48.440 --> 00:06:52.440 line:1
The screen fills with a browser showing
a video on YouTube.

00:06:53.885 --> 00:06:57.885 line:1
Beneath the video appears a title: Brian
Eno - The BIg Ship - DOTS extended edit.

00:07:09.224 --> 00:07:13.224
A web browser appears showing a Google
search being typed.

00:07:13.628 --> 00:07:16.558
Search results fill the screen.

00:07:16.673 --> 00:07:18.633
The cursor loads a poem
from the results.

00:07:18.947 --> 00:07:22.947
A title appears on screen:
Fourth Metaphor: Mixing.

00:07:24.156 --> 00:07:28.156
A cursor begins to type: When composers
use multiple modes as tools for thinking

00:07:28.156 --> 00:07:34.276
rather than just to visually illustrate
a completed script, they actually

00:07:34.276 --> 00:07:42.586
generate new meaning. Creation of a
digital video then can become much more

00:07:42.586 --> 00:07:47.266
than an act
of "translation" or transcription. . . .

00:07:47.266 --> 00:07:55.143 line:1
Compositing and new recursivity . . . are
also critical cognitive experiences. . . .

00:08:04.003 --> 00:08:08.003 line:1
A video editor appears showing
a student project.

00:08:10.692 --> 00:08:14.692 line:1
Cloud imagery fills the screen.

00:08:21.474 --> 00:08:25.474
The playhead moves in the editor as
images appear.

00:08:28.581 --> 00:08:32.581
The imagery in the editor shows
underwater and aerial footage.

00:08:41.204 --> 00:08:45.204
A new video editor fills the screen
showing a student project.

00:08:47.589 --> 00:08:51.589
The editor show an image of a
water dropletoverlaid with text:

00:08:51.649 --> 00:08:53.709
Now I am a lake.

00:08:54.744 --> 00:08:58.204
The image is put in motion, and
the droplet splashes on the lake surface

00:08:58.600 --> 00:09:02.600
The editor shows text:
A woman bends over me.

00:09:03.343 --> 00:09:07.343 line:1
the editor shows a woman's face
overlaid on the lake surface

00:09:07.962 --> 00:09:10.562 line:1
The cursor hovers over the woman's eye.

00:09:17.692 --> 00:09:22.732 line:1
The image is put in motion: the droplet
splashes and the woman's eye opens.

00:09:25.404 --> 00:09:28.544 line:1
A new video editor fills the screen
showing a student project.

00:09:31.078 --> 00:09:35.078 line:1
In the editor, the cursor moves the
playhead in the timeline.

00:09:38.806 --> 00:09:40.436 line:1
The cursor presses play.

00:09:45.566 --> 00:09:49.566
The editor shows a blend of underwater
and cloud imagery.

00:09:54.000 --> 00:09:58.000 line:1
Title on screen:
Last Metaphor: Resistance.

00:10:00.667 --> 00:10:04.407 line:1
A cursor types: Only the humanities and
social science articles . . . contained

00:10:04.407 --> 00:10:14.755 line:1
reporting verbs characterizing the source
as unreliable (e.g., fail, overlook,

00:10:14.755 --> 00:10:21.455 line:1
exaggerate, or ignore). This is
attributed to the "more disputational

00:10:21.455 --> 00:10:25.455 line:1
style of argument" found
in the soft knowledge fields.

00:10:32.539 --> 00:10:37.739 line:1
The screen fades to white, then a cursor
types: The current model of digital

00:10:37.739 --> 00:10:45.879 line:1
video composing as a sequential series
of temporally-discrete steps is predicated

00:10:45.879 --> 00:10:53.129 line:1
on the logic of old media and, thus, may
no longer be sufficient to account for

00:10:53.129 --> 00:11:02.309 line:1
the new media composing processes
that emerge with new media interfaces.

00:11:10.471 --> 00:11:14.471 line:1
A video editor fills the screen showing
a student project.

00:11:15.377 --> 00:11:19.287 line:1
In the editor, the cursor presses play and
the playhead moves over the timeline.

00:11:21.423 --> 00:11:25.423 line:1
Imagery of a bird hovering above grass
appears in the video editor.

00:11:26.856 --> 00:11:30.856 line:1
The bird slowly flaps its wings
and hovers

00:11:39.127 --> 00:11:42.257 line:1
In the editor, the student project
shows text:

00:11:42.307 --> 00:11:45.617 line:1
Because they liked me "still" --
They put me in the Closet --

00:11:49.207 --> 00:11:52.577 line:1
In the editor the project shows a callout:
Matt Wood Cinematographer,

00:11:52.577 --> 00:11:55.387 line:1
"Bird in Flight,"
http://vimeo.com/69825194.

00:12:03.388 --> 00:12:07.388 line:1
The cursor scrolls through the timeline
in the video editor.

00:12:10.588 --> 00:12:13.588 line:1
The screen fades to a white background and
a cursor types:

00:12:13.588 --> 00:12:18.818 line:1
Craft criticism . . . foregrounds textual
production while backgrounding textual

00:12:18.818 --> 00:12:25.882 line:1
interpretation. . . . Craft criticism uses
methods of production to examine the ways

00:12:25.882 --> 00:12:34.082 line:1
imaginative literature operatesâ€”and how
it can help its authors and audience

00:12:34.082 --> 00:12:39.675 line:1
members engage critically with the
cultural environment that surrounds them.

00:12:48.092 --> 00:12:51.542 line:1
The screen fills with a video showing
an animated sea otter.

00:12:51.898 --> 00:12:54.858 line:1
The otter wears an eye patch
and a pirate hat.

00:12:58.747 --> 00:13:01.347 line:1
The otter appears in front of a laptop.

00:13:01.714 --> 00:13:03.787 line:1
A callout slides on screen titled:
Fair Use.

00:13:03.927 --> 00:13:06.547 line:1
Rapid typing in the callout reproduces
the spoken text.

00:13:06.640 --> 00:13:10.180 line:1
The otter pushes the callout
partially off screen.

00:13:12.739 --> 00:13:17.599 line:1
The cursor types the spoken text.

00:13:24.928 --> 00:13:28.928 line:1
The screen fills with a bird flying
in slow motion over grass.

00:13:29.902 --> 00:13:33.592 line:1
The bird slowly flaps its wings

00:13:37.468 --> 00:13:39.678 line:1
The video with the
slow flying bird shows text:

00:13:39.726 --> 00:13:41.716 line:1
As when a little Girl.

00:13:42.875 --> 00:13:46.016 line:1
Because they liked me "still" --
They put me in the Closet --

00:13:50.330 --> 00:13:53.820 line:1
The bird flaps slowly, hovering
over dry grass.

00:13:57.942 --> 00:14:00.362 line:1
The video on screen cuts to a
grey sky from below.

00:14:00.451 --> 00:14:03.233 line:1
The video shows text:
Still! Could themself have peeped --

00:14:03.955 --> 00:14:06.265 line:1
Starlings swarm against the sky.

00:14:06.390 --> 00:14:09.810 line:1
The video shows text:
And seen my Brain -- go round

00:14:10.343 --> 00:14:14.028 line:1
Flocks of starlings swarm
against the sky.

00:14:15.922 --> 00:14:19.652 line:1
The video shows text:
They might as wise have lodged a Bird

00:14:19.774 --> 00:14:22.494 line:1
For Treason -- in the Pound --

00:14:24.456 --> 00:14:28.456 line:1
Works cited scroll on screen